{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Emergence refers to the phenomenon where the behavior of the system is implicitly induced rather than explicitly constructed (Bommasani et al., 2021).",
    "In other words, emergence occurs when quantitative changes in a system result in qualitative changes in behavior (Anderson, 1972).",
    "In terms of moral competence, emergence is demonstrated by the fact that LLMs can generate new text concerning moral judgment, but it is currently impossible to explain what text they will produce.",
    "Homogenization implies that the integration of machine learning systems in a wide range of applications provides powerful leverage for many tasks while also creating single point failures (Bommasani et al., 2021).",
    "In the context of LLMs, homogenization refers to the similarity in model construction methods."
  ],
